        "The distribution network service providers (DNSPs) in South East and regional Queensland are Energex and Ergon, both owned by Energy Queensland (EQL). Gladstone sits within Ergon's network and is supplied by three bulk supply points – Gladstone South, Gladstone North, and Boat Creek – feeding nine zone substations.",
